<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-22T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-22T06:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1406:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-22T14:00:00+03:00">April 22,
                                1944—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received April 23—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1395. I informed Vyshinski on April 21 of the contents of the Department’s
                        937, April 17 and left with him a memorandum on the subject which included a
                        statement inquiring whether the Soviet Government would issue a statement
                        expressing its attitude concerning Nazi atrocities. Vyshinski replied that
                        the Soviet Government had frequently expressed its position on this subject,
                        however he would bring the memorandum to the attention of his Government and
                        give the matter his personal study.<note n="7" xml:id="d595fn7">Soviet
                            action in this matter was not obtained.</note>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>